cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper focuses on scene recognition using convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and specifically addresses the use of RGB-D data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the training strategy and architecture modifications for CNNs, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach for learning depth-specific features, which could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of end-to-end network optimization and multilayer classifiers could also fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the combination of RGB and depth features, which could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia).
